Description: Body sherd of Chian pottery open vessel, probably a chalice; white slip; interior glazed streaky black with single band in added white; exterior: glaze bands alternating with sets of three dilute lines.
Curator's comments: For parallels regarding the exterior decoration, see the laconising cup, British Museum 1886,0401.1283.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.2063) (phase 2)
